.TH HELPR 1 "September 2025" "helpr 1.5.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
helpr \- cheat-style command reference tool

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B helpr
[\fIOPTION\fR] \fIPAGE\fR

.SH DESCRIPTION
helpr displays short usage examples for commands.
Pages are stored system-wide and per-user.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -l, --list
List pages.

.TP
.B -s TERM
Search pages.

.TP
.B -e PAGE
Edit or extend a page.

.SH CONFIG
Config order:
defaults → /etc/helpr/config → ~/.config/helpr/config → env vars

.SH COMMANDS
helpr config edit | set | get | list | reset
helpr doctor
helpr uninstall [--backup|--purge]

.SH FILES
/usr/share/helpr/pages
~/.config/helpr/pages
/etc/helpr/config
~/.config/helpr/config

